      "comment_id" : 127745515,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "There is absolutely no reason to do any of this. You&#39;re attempting to shave off each digit from the integer <i>backwards</i>, convert each digit to a character manually, append each digit <i>one at a time</i> to the string builder, before reversing the whole thing to get the original ordering back. <b>Why?</b> A <code>StringBuilder</code> can just <b>accept the whole integer in one call to append!</b> And it works across all the special cases your code fails for. You can replace this entire thing with <code>StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(); sb.append(intValue); return sb.toString();</code>"
